            <div class='post' itemprop='text'>
              <p>Hi Josh,</p>
<p>I +1 your request, since I need Brazilian states maps in my work. I‚Äôve tried to build my Redash development VM but I wasn‚Äôt  able to do it quickly so I decided to improvise:</p>
<ul>
<li>I‚Äôve downloaded a Brazil‚Äôs GeoJSON file and renamed it to countries.geo.json</li>
<li>Then I changed the name of the fields in order to match original‚Äôs fields in countries.geo.json</li>
<li>Finally I replaced the old file in /opt/redash/current/client/dist/data (0962607.countries.geo.json) with the new one</li>
</ul>
<p>It worked like a charm! Unfortunately this was only a workaround because I‚Äôll need new maps from each state in Brazil‚Ä¶</p>
<p>Greetings,</p>
<p>Arnaldo</p>
            </div>

